#DOC id=04--agents source=/root/yvon/docs/briefs/lifeos-reference/04--agents.md format=toon-doc compressed=2026-06-12T06:40:26.297Z

S|# 04 · Agents|> An infrastructure overview: which agents run on which machine, what they have access to, and the health of the fleet.
S|Purpose|A single place to keep an overview of the agt fleet across the owner's physical machines — what's running where, access, and connectivity — with a direct line (SSH/screen share) to fix machines when needed.
S|Page header|- Title: **Agents**, breadcrumb `Vibe with AI / Agents`. // - A "Find an agt or machine…" search and a link to the **Org Chart**. // - Top bar: **System healthy**, **agents live** counter.
S|Top summary cards (fleet stats)|A row of KPI cards across the top: // - **Machines online** — e.g. `3` (Mac minis online). // - **Agents running** — e.g. `23`. // - **Used RAM** — e.g. `48 GB` (with a fraction of total). // - **Routing / gateway** — e.g. **Hermes** (the routing/gateway agt).
S|Machine groups (the fleet)|Agents are grouped under the physical machine they run on. Each machine block shows the machine name, role, status (online/cooling/idle), and the agt avatars on it: // - **Mac Mini 2 — Hermes** · *Personal Layer · serves all workspaces.* Hosts the **routing/gateway** and the **personal team**: **Nexus** (CTO), **Steve** (QA), **Knox** (sec), **Wolf** (fin), Henry (Chief of Staff). Status chips like "routing / online." // - **Mac Mini 1 — OpenClaw** · *Workspace tier · produces the work.* Hosts t
S|What it's for (design intent)|This is a monitoring/overview page — keep an eye on which machine hosts which agents, RAM/health, and connectivity. It is the tec counterpart to the **Org Chart** (which shows the *organizational* structure rather than the *hardware* layout). See `27-hardware-and-runtime.md` for the runtime details.